The General Public Law as published by the Personal Sovereignty Foundation is a generalization of the religious goals of the FSF's GNU [[General Public License]] into the realm of the physical, tangible, material world.

Proposed [[Object]] User [[Instance]] DEED:
As a free object user you MAY:
<ol start="0">
<li> Use this instance for any purpose.</li>
<li> Modify this instance by [[Rent]]ing or buying the [[Physical Sources]] needed for that modification.</li>
<li> Copy this instance by renting or buying the physical sources needed for that production.</li>
<li> Share this instance or a copy - whether modified or not.</li>
</ol>
If you share this object instance or a copy - whether modified or not, you MUST:
<ol type="A">
<li>Accompany each instance with a copy of this DEED.</li>
<li>Treat all [[Profit]] gained through the sale of this object or through the rental of physical sources as an investment from that user toward more physical sources.</li>
<li>Issue [[GNUrho]] currency against those physical sources.</li>
</ol>
*[[Profit]] separates from [[Wage]] as [[Owner]]s hire Workers.

